I have written down the loot I've gotten from each PoP zone and how much each item sells for to a vendor. Some items are 70 pp, some items are 1 pp. It varies. I would make sure if the group was splitting up soon, I would ask them to stop exp'ing 10 minutes early and wait for me to sell stuff to the vendor (group would port out with me) so I could split the money.<br>
<br>
In a situation where someone has to leave, but they'll get replaced by someone else, I look over my inventory and have a good idea of how much &quot;value&quot; I've accumulated and will generally give the departing person an item (or more) that is equivalent to his/her share of the split.<br>
<br>
I have heard of people bringing a lot of plat on them (say 600 pp for example) ahead of time and when the group is going to break up, they figure out how much loot amounts up to and use their personal money for the split. That way they can sell the stuff later so members can walk away happy.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=truthreason>TruthReason</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm actually Goanad.</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/5/02 7:18:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3506.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problem is sis</span><hr size=1> I see clerics covering dots is important. I mean, why should they have to pay for you(a non cleric) to play, sort of? Those dots add up and get expensive. <br>
